00002  * ir_DistanceProtocol.hpp
00003  *
00004  * This decoder tries to decode a pulse width or pulse distance protocol.
00005  * 1. Analyze all space and mark length
00006  * 2. Decide if we have an pulse width or distance protocol
00007  * 3. Try to decode with the mark and space data found in step 1
00008  * No data and address decoding, only raw data as result.
00009  *
00010  * Pulse distance data can be sent with the generic function:
00011  * void sendPulseDistanceWidthData(unsigned int aOneMarkMicros, unsigned int aOneSpaceMicros, unsigned int aZeroMarkMicros,
00012  *            unsigned int aZeroSpaceMicros, uint32_t aData, uint8_t aNumberOfBits, bool aMSBfirst, bool aSendStopBit = false)
00013  * The header must be sent manually with:
00014  *          IrSender.mark(MarkMicros)
00015  *          IrSender.space(SpaceMicros);
00016  * see also: SendDemo example line 150
00017  *
